The paper deals with the detection problem of binary faster-than-Nyquist (FTN) signaling, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM). The proposed sequence estimation technique is based on sphere decoding (SD), which is a common technique used in wireless communication systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the potential benefits of FTN signaling in terms of data rate and spectral efficiency, which are topics related to signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
